
// The code changes the name of the first [to] node within the [message] node of the [mail.smtp.send] invocation to the value of the [name] node found in the [.arguments] node. It uses [set-name] to rename nodes and [get-value] to retrieve the current value of the [name] node.
set-name:x:../*/mail.smtp.send/*/message/*/to/0
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/name
